text: Sebastian Giustinian was a sixteenth-century Venetian diplomat. Between 1515 and 1519, during the reign of Henry VIII of England, Giustinian was the Venetian ambassador to England.Suzannah Lipscomb, 1536: The Year That Changed Henry VIII, p.30 ==References== Category:Year of birth missing Category:16th- century deaths Category:Year of death missing Category:People of the Tudor period Category:People from Venice Category:16th-century Italian people Category:Ambassadors of the Republic of Venice to England Category:16th- century diplomats
